cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on a downlink OFDM communication system with dynamic user demands, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with uncertain sensing spectrum resources and time-varying channel conditions, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.GT (Game Theory) - The profit maximization problem can be viewed as a game between the virtual network operator and the users, making game theory a likely sub-category. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes on-line control policies for pricing and resource scheduling, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The use of OFDM communication system and heterogenous users suggest that multimedia may be a relevant sub-category.
